<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 13:35:47 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>巨大的热带树木如何将水输送到 70 米，以保持与小树一样的抗旱能力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/how-giant-tropical-trees-transport-water-70-meters-to-stay-as-drought-resilient-as-smaller-trees</link><description>热带森林的巨树因其储存碳的能力而成为应对气候变化的重要盟友，但科学界对它们的了解仍然很少。然而，一项研究&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-giant-tropical-trees-transport-water-70-meters-to-stay-as-drought-resilient-as-smaller-trees.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 13:35:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/how-giant-tropical-trees-transport-water-70-meters-to-stay-as-drought-resilient-as-smaller-trees</guid></item><item><title>纳米酶无需基因工程即可绘制活细胞内纳米颗粒的路线</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/nanozymes-map-nanoparticle-routes-inside-live-cells-without-genetic-engineering</link><description>纳米颗粒广泛应用于医学领域，将药物、基因或显像剂输送到身体的特定部位。然而，一旦纳米颗粒到达细胞，就会发生很多事情——它可以到达目标、被降解、与帮助运输的蛋白质相互作用，或者与阻碍其运输的蛋白质相互作用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nanozymes-map-nanoparticle-routes-inside-live-cells-without-genetic-engineering.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 13:20:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/nanozymes-map-nanoparticle-routes-inside-live-cells-without-genetic-engineering</guid></item><item><title>中微子的怪异可能完全改写粒子物理学</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/the-weirdness-of-neutrinos-could-completely-rewrite-particle-physics</link><description>一位哲学家提出了重新思考如何在粒子物理标准模型中定义粒子的论点&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-weirdness-of-neutrinos-could-completely-rewrite-particle-physics.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 13:05:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/the-weirdness-of-neutrinos-could-completely-rewrite-particle-physics</guid></item><item><title>双活动髋关节置换植入物可将脱位风险降低 70%</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/dual-mobility-hip-replacement-implant-can-lower-dislocation-risk-by-70</link><description>一项涉及瑞典和英国 44 家医院 1,600 名患者的新研究表明，新型髋关节置换植入物可将手术后关节脱位的风险降低 70%，该研究发表于&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dual-mobility-hip-replacement-implant-can-lower-dislocation-risk-by-702.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 12:50:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/dual-mobility-hip-replacement-implant-can-lower-dislocation-risk-by-70</guid></item><item><title>首次强调“死亡浪潮”的大脑动力学</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/brain-dynamics-of-the-wave-of-death-highlighted-for-the-first-time</link><description>2023 年，巴黎大脑研究所的科学家们研究了神经科学中最令人着迷且令人不安的转变之一：当大脑缺氧时，皮质会发生什么变化。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-dynamics-of-the-wave-of-death-highlighted-for-the-first-time.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 12:35:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/brain-dynamics-of-the-wave-of-death-highlighted-for-the-first-time</guid></item><item><title>就连小岛秀夫也担心“数字数据将不再属于个人”，我们对艺术的接触“可能会突然被切断”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/even-hideo-kojima-is-afraid-that-digital-data-will-no-longer-be-owned-by-individuals-and-that-access-to-art-that-we-love-may-suddenly-be-cut-off</link><description>“委员会认为，现阶段它不能提出法律义务，要求视频游戏在停止商业提供后保持其可玩性。这也是由于现有的知识产权。根据欧盟版权法，权利持有人对其创作享有专有权。” &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/even-hideo-kojima-is-afraid-that-digital-data-will-no-longer-be-owned-by-individuals-and-that-access-to-art-that-we-love-may-suddenly-be-cut-off.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 12:20:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/even-hideo-kojima-is-afraid-that-digital-data-will-no-longer-be-owned-by-individuals-and-that-access-to-art-that-we-love-may-suddenly-be-cut-off</guid></item><item><title>科学家称太阳可能最终不会吞噬地球</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/the-sun-may-not-engulf-earth-after-all-scientists-say</link><description>科学家表示，地球可能不会被垂死的太阳不断膨胀的火球吞没，而这长期以来一直被认为是我们地球家园的最终命运。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-sun-may-not-engulf-earth-after-all-scientists-say.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 12:05:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/the-sun-may-not-engulf-earth-after-all-scientists-say</guid></item><item><title>湿咖啡渣在短短 90 秒内变成高级固体燃料</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/wet-coffee-grounds-turned-into-high-grade-solid-fuel-in-just-90-seconds</link><description>韩国地球科学与矿产资源研究所 (KIGAM) 的一个研究团队开发了一种技术，只需 90 秒即可将湿废咖啡渣直接转化为高质量生物炭，无需干燥或除油。这一突破提供了一条快速、节能的途径，将高水分有机废物转化为有价值的燃料和碳材料。这项研究由 Taejun Park 博士领导，与 GodTech Co., Ltd. 合作，发表在世界领先的化学工程期刊之一《化学工程杂志》上。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/wet-coffee-grounds-turned-into-high-grade-solid-fuel-in-just-90-seconds2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 11:50:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/wet-coffee-grounds-turned-into-high-grade-solid-fuel-in-just-90-seconds</guid></item><item><title>我需要支付或放弃股权才能成为 5050 的一部分吗？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/do-i-need-to-pay-or-give-up-equity-to-be-part-of-5050</link><description>5050帮助伟大的科学家和工程师创办和建立深度科技初创公司。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/do-i-need-to-pay-or-give-up-equity-to-be-part-of-5050.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 11:35:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/do-i-need-to-pay-or-give-up-equity-to-be-part-of-5050</guid></item><item><title>尽管损耗极大，仍观察到多模光的量子特性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/quantum-properties-of-multimode-light-observed-despite-extreme-losses</link><description>光的量子特性极其微妙。当研究人员试图测量它们时，即使在到达探测器的途中出现很小的损失也会使它们变得不可见，从而限制了它们在严格控制的环境之外的使用。马克斯·普朗克光科学研究所 (MPL) 的科学家组成的一个研究合作小组展示了一种新方法，可以同时测量多个光量子通道并揭示它们的纠缠，即使几乎所有光在到达探测器之前都已丢失。结果， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-properties-of-multimode-light-observed-despite-extreme-losses2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 11:20:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/quantum-properties-of-multimode-light-observed-despite-extreme-losses</guid></item></channel></rss>